<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I dont claim to know that much about the sorcerer still, as I am only level 20 myself, but I remember being in the dungeon in camelot hills at about your level and also feeling like an xp leach.<P>I seem to remember things getting better when I got the higer level spells, after all, if you are level 7, using banish will(a level 2 debuff) on a level 8 9 or 10th mob then I really would expect to get resisted more.<P>Dont know how much the level 4 mindblast spell hits for but even now at 20 I use level 8 mindblast and hit for between 35-53 dd for a piddly ammount of mana and a 2 second delay.<P>Crowd Control in small areas is always tough but something that is, as far as I am concerned, worth practising. Dunno what view you are using but an external mobile camera is useful for targeting and f8 can cycle through the mobs your fighting if you really cant click on them, though if they are the same name you might not be able to tell if you have targeted an already mezzed mob.<P>When in groups where mobs are being taken down really quickly I forget about the debuffs or just put one of them on at the begining, bear in mind the *range* of the debuff, we have a lot of aoe ones that would wake up mezzes or even pull others into the fight.<P>As for the speccing I am taking mind up the watoosie and, against all advice form everyone going to go for the full compliment of spells in mind spec. think I have had a charm resisted about 4 times up to level 20 and mezz resists are at about 4 or 5% on yellow-red. <P>Btw dont underestimate confusion, I have found it to be very useful. <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P><BR>Just my opinin and good luck<P>Babayaga
