<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
1) Yes, I think that most quests that are appropriate for your level can fairly easily be completed by a small group.  There are some exceptions (the thinking cap quest is challenging if you get it when you are first eligible, even with a small group).  But by and large, I think this is because the quests are balanced so that an individual can complete them.  Thus, when you take several people, they are easier  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>2) I am 2/3 spec body/mind, and I too noticed an increased in resistance rates of MOBs to charm as I leveled.  There are several factors here -- your level, MOB level, the type of MOB, and maybe your specialization level in mind, that contribute to resistance.  I think that if you cast "mez" first and then charm the MOB, you'll be safer.<P>3) Yes, we can feel like we don't have a real role sometimes in dungeons.  Practice mezzing -- it's tough at times in dungeons, but VERY useful.  You also have amnesia to save your healer if she / he draws aggro.  I also think that you will find that your mind blast spells do a fair amount of damage, but that depends on how high you are specialized in body.  I have found that at lower levels I tended to do comparable damage to some of the tanks, although a full fire wizard will always out-nuke us.  Your DOT spell also helps tick down the health of the MOB.  Finally, at high levels, when you goto Barrows dungeon, for example, you will be able to find a pet (there are goblins there).  It's a pain to keep them with you at times, but at least you can find one  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
