<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I'm at level 16 right now and have either 12 or 13 in mind right now. Decided to play around and trained matter up to about level 5 when I hit 14. Gah! was that a mistake. I've noticed I've had a terrible time charming even level mobs (if they're a level below me but still yellow I don't seem to have this problem). It usualy takes at least 2 tries with tomb raiders, Nymphs and Forest trackers (think it's the trackers).<P>Matter of fact I had a Tracker who was at about 1/2 health after fighting boulderlings and was planning on running back to Camelot to work on my tailoring. (I had been up to Swansons for a supply run on materials). So I thought I'd pull Bullseye's stunt from his strategy guide and put 2 yellows against an orange.<P>Ok found an ornange close to a yellow both within casting range "great" I thought. Started pet twards Orange, Cast a str/con debuff and then the pet engaged him. Waited for pet to hit once, then cast a DOT. Instantly switched targets to the fresh Yellow, hit release, and cast Charm. "You failed to charm the target" I'm like ok no sweat...Cast again "You fail to charm the target"...Now I'm thinking uh-oh..and at that point *whack* I get hit. My first pet was dead and the Orange decided he didn't like what I did, and wanted revenge on me. Ok now at this point I panick, I hit quickcast-Mes (It's instinctutal when I get hit    <IMG SRC="rolleyes.gif" border="0"> ) of course I get the message "Your spell fails, the mob is enraged" (Hey, at least I got a quick trip back to Camelot to get back to my tailoring)Even if I had gotten a Qucik-Charm to stick, I think it wouldn't have mattered because I was dead in 3 hits and he was only down 1/2 life. There's no way the new pet would have been able to draw agro off of me, or kill him in that time.<P>ANYWAY I've learned my lesson from this. Last level I had a lot of leftover points but am saving them. Soon as I hit 17 I'm putting 2 levels into Mind.<P>Something I plan on doing Just before I leevl is to go ahead and experiment on the forest trackers to get a more exact number on charming success and the levels of the mob. Then after I level and put 2 levels into mind try again and see the difference. I'll post the results here with what I find.<P>--------------------<P>It's not a dress damnit! It's a Fine Manly Robe!!
