<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
On the issue of resistance and whether it relates to skill level, here's my input.  I remain uncertain of whether skill level affects the rate of MOB resistance.  God, I have said that a million times   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  But I am, increasingly, thinking that it DOES affect resistance.<P>But -- here's the good news.  I, too, noticed increased resistance on charms in the levels from the mid-teens into the 20's.  This was when, in staggering my skills as I built mind and body to 2/3, my mind would sometimes lag behind my level.<P>But -- when I got into the 30's, even though I was still keeping mind/body at 2/3 (staggered a bit in favor of mind so that I could maintain an even-con pet), I noticed that the increased resistance was seemingly disappearing.  I think that what is happening is that as we increase in power, the difference in specialization is less significant ("diminishing returns"), which likely means that 2/3 specialization at higher levels will work just fine and WILL NOT cause a significantly greater number of resists (as it did in those middle levels).  That's probably why Mythic has felt OK in recommending 2/3 specialization as the way to go (or at least as the most flexible design).<P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
